  <chapter id="intro">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <sect1>
      <title>Scope of this document</title>
      <para>
        This document describes the commands and functions available to operators in
        the ircd-seven IRC daemon.
      </para>
      <para>
        This document, and various ideas for features of ircd-seven, have
        been taken from dancer-ircd/hyperion, the ircd used on freenode,
        mainly written by Andrew Suffield and Jilles Tjoelker.
      </para>
      <para>
        While this document may be of some interest to the users of ircd-seven servers,
        it is intended as a reference for network staff.
      </para>
      <para>
        ircd-seven is based on charybdis-2.1, although much has changed.
        <ulink url="http://ircd-charybdis.org">ircd-charybdis</ulink> is currently used
        on <ulink url="http://www.atheme.net">AthemeNet</ulink>, amongst others.
      </para>
    </sect1>
  </chapter>
